Key Match Events: The match ended 0-0, with Kamberipa and Kazapua scoring for Namibia in the 50th and 72nd minutes respectively.
Pre-Game Insights: Namibia aim to continue their undefeated start to World Cup qualifying when they host Tunisia at Orlando Stadium on Sunday.
Tunisia could create separation from their hosts in Johannesburg, keen to remain one of the nations with a 100% record in the qualifying series.
With Peter Shalulile not in the Namibia squad, the Brave Warriors must find goals from elsewhere in the side against the North Africans.
Youssef Msakni has netted two of Tunisia's goals in qualifying but the 33-year-old wide attacker's absence could further limit Tunisia's goalscoring threat.
Post-Match Reflections: The match ended 0-0, with both sides unable to break the deadlock.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Namibia's goalless run since their win over Tunisia in January was extended.
Tunisia's sequence of clean sheets in Group H was maintained.
The match was played at Orlando Stadium.
Others: Namibia's possible starting lineup included Kazapua, Ikeinge, Hambira, Kamberipa, Hanamub, Karuuombe, Petrus, Namib, Kasume, Hotto, and Kalula.
Tunisia's possible starting lineup included Said, Mathlouthi, Meriah, Talbi, Abdi, Romdhane, Skhiri, Ghandri, Rafia, Achouri, and Saad.
